<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     FAQ
     Expandable accordion using <details>/<summary>.
     Six placeholder questions.
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Everything you need to know.</p>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What is mnemospark and what does it do?</summary>
        <p>mnemospark is an OpenClaw plugin and backend service that lets you run cloud operations and file storage workflows. You can quote storage, upload/download/list/delete files. Your agent pays for storage with its wallet using USDC on Base.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What is a wallet on Base?</summary>
        <p>A Base wallet is a blockchain account (address + private key) on the Base network. It can hold USDC and sign transactions/authorizations used for payments.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How does mnemospark provide a wallet?</summary>
        <p>During setup, mnemospark creates or reuses a local wallet key and uses it to sign payment/auth requests. The wallet key is stored locally in your OpenClaw home directory (for example under <code>~/.openclaw/mnemospark/wallet</code>).</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How do I fund my wallet on Base?</summary>
        <p>Send USDC (Base network) to your wallet address from an exchange or another wallet. Make sure you select Base as the network when withdrawing/transferring. Once funded, mnemospark can use those funds for payments.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How do I pay for storage?</summary>
        <p>mnemospark requests a storage quote first, then submits a signed USDC payment authorization (x402 flow) when you execute upload/storage actions. Payment and storage requests are tied together by the quote.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>When do I pay for storage?</summary>
        <p>Your agent submits payment on the 1st of each month via a cron job. Payment is required each month to keep storage active.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Where is my data stored?</summary>
        <p>Files are securely stored with the selected cloud provider. Currently only AWS is supported. You may select which geographic region your data is stored in when creating a quote. Hint — pick the region closest to you.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How is my data protected?</summary>
        <p>mnemospark's upload flow uses encrypted payloads (AES-256-GCM) and request signing. Access to storage endpoints requires wallet-proof authentication and signed requests. Your agent's wallet is its ID. Keep your wallet safe! Never give out your wallet private key.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How can I access my stored data?</summary>
        <p>Use mnemospark commands to list, download, and delete files. Access is gated by wallet-proof authorization. Your agent's wallet is its ID. Keep your wallet safe! Never give out your wallet private key.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

